        <updateDate>2024-08-07T20:26:01Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Improving Access to Medicare Coverage Act of </strong><strong>2024</strong></p><p>This bill deems an individual receiving outpatient observation services in a hospital as an inpatient for purposes of satisfying the three-day inpatient hospital-stay requirement&nbsp;with respect to&nbsp;Medicare coverage of skilled nursing facility (SNF) services. (Generally, individuals must have been an inpatient at a hospital for at least three days in order to qualify for SNF services. An individual's time spent under observation at a hospital for purposes of determining whether the individual should be admitted does not count towards this requirement.)</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
